{{nihongo|'''''Yakuza Apocalypse'''''|極道大戦争|'''Gokudō Daisensō'''}} is a 2015 Japanese [[Action film|action]] [[Fantasy film|fantasy]]–[[Yakuza film|yakuza]] [[Vampire film|vampire]] film directed by [[Takashi Miike]] and starring [[Hayato Ichihara]], [[Yayan Ruhian]], and [[Riko Narumi]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.filmbiz.asia/news/miike-to-battle-yakuza-vampires|title= Miike to battle yakuza vampires|author= Kevin Ma|date= 18 April 2014|accessdate= 29 April 2014|work= [[Film Business Asia]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allcinema.net/prog/show_c.php?num_c=351661|script-title=ja:映画 極道大戦争|accessdate=2015-06-20|publisher=Stingray|work=allcinema|language=Japanese}}</ref> It was written by Yoshitaka Yamaguchi. It premiered at the [[2015 Cannes Film Festival|Cannes Film Festival]] on May 21, 2015, before being released theatrically on June 20 throughout Japan.

==Cast==
* [[Hayato Ichihara]] as Akira Kageyama
* [[Yayan Ruhian]] as Kyoken (狂犬) / Mad Dog
* [[Riko Narumi]] as Kyōko Anan
* [[Lily Franky]] as Genyō Kamiura
* [[Reiko Takashima]]

==Production==
Production on the film began on 17 April 2014. The film features Indonesian actor and stunt choreographer Yayan Ruhian, who had previously costarred in ''[[The Raid (2011 film)|The Raid]]'' and ''[[The Raid 2]]''. It marks his first foray into acting outside of his native Indonesia.

==Reception==
The film received mixed to positive reviews from critics. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has a 58% rating, based on 31 reviews.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/yakuza_apocalypse/ | title=Yakuza Apocalypse (2015) | work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] | publisher=[[Flixster]] | accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] reports a 62 out of 100 rating, based on 14 critics, indicating "generally favorable reviews".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/yakuza-apocalypse | title=Yakuza Apocalypse reviews | work=[[Metacritic]] | publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] | accessdate=11 December 2015}}</ref>

